description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adult nurses looking for opportunities in Orthopaedics and Trauma Assessment Unit, our Orthopaedics and Trauma Assessment Unit could be just the place for you!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward T7 is a busy Orthopaedic and Trauma Assessment Unit and is supported by a very experienced trauma assessment team. We are a friendly, supportive and patient focused team who work quickly and efficiently to ensure our patients are cared for in a safe and efficient manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would love you to join us in a ward environment that will encourage you to develop your nursing and clinical skills, broaden your knowledge of orthopaedic care and orthopaedic interventions as well as being supported in putting the heart of the patients at the forefront of everything you do. If the excitement of being a skilled nurse in a fast paced trauma unit or alternatively on the ward ensuring your call to nursing and your passion as a nurse can be brought to fruition in delivering compassionate care, then this is the ward for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OUR COMMITMENT TO YOU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An excellent preceptorship programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wide variety of learning and development opportunities including in-house training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Link Nurse opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development and specialism in orthopaedics/ trauma assessment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Secondments or rotations with other areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support from senior nurses in your future career&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working – a variety of shift patterns on both days and nights are available&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to a large variety of orthopaedic specialties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOUR VALUED CONTRIBUTION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic, patient focussed nurses who are able to work within a team setting to deliver exceptional care to our patients. An ability to think and act quickly as well as being adaptable to changing situations will be of benefit in our fast paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’d welcome the opportunity to meet with you to show you what working with our brilliant teams could mean for your future career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For overseas nurses, we welcome your application but please ask that you provide confirmation of IELT&#39;s/OET pass, CBT, NMC decision letter and have OSCE training/examination arranged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our team purpose is that we strive for quality care that is compassionate and how we would want our loved ones cared for. We define ourselves as a friendly team that is respectful, kind, equal and patient centred. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We meet regular as a team and strive to ensure that we meet our team purpose. Our team journey can be followed on twitter @T7Troh&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In line with the Trust’s Single Equality Scheme we welcome applications from everyone irrespective of ethnic origin, disability, age, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability, nationality, religion, marital status, social back ground or trade union membership. However, as members of ethnicity minority groups and individuals with disabilities are currently under-represented at this level of post, we would encourage applications from members of these groups. Appointment will be based on merit alone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Emma Butts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Lead Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address emma.butts@pat.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 07970199152 &lt;/p&gt;
